						<summary>

						<p>Stone lying near a wall in the village.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara: Rāmadēvarāya.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1545 (expired), Dundubhi, Mārgaśira śu. 12, Wednesday,</hi> corresponding to 1622 A.D., December 4.</p>						

						<p>Much damaged. It records a grant of land by Pemmaśani Timmānāyuḍu to Chevāku Gōpaya for having dug and built a well.</p>						

						</summary>
